% parrot0 social register — conversational markers as knowledge.
% Loaded at brain_create so the self-model can query which markers exist;
% the C code reads these facts at runtime instead of hardcoding word lists.
% Predicates: social_marker/2, social_pattern/2, question_word/1, reaction_word/1.

% --- token-level social markers (whole-word match) ---





% --- cue-based patterns (substring match in normalized text) ---




% gen124: casual small-talk openers the chatsim transcripts kept walling on —
% phatic contact, not information requests. Patterns are matched against the
% CANONICALIZED text, so "whats up" appears here as its expansion "what is up"
% (gen74 contraction map), while the apostrophe form "what's up" is left intact.

% --- question words (signal an information request) ---


% --- reaction words (laughter/conversational fillers) ---

% --- gen225 (basic-chat cat.1): phatic speech acts (EN + IT) ---
% Recognized PHRASES live here; the REPLIES live as response_template(type, …)
% in kb/core/responses.p0. Both are KB knowledge so the classes grow at runtime
% with no code edit; the C only knows the structural list of act TYPES.

% valediction for the night (kept distinct from a plain goodbye)

% felicitation / congratulation / festive greeting

% well-wishing (luck, recovery, parting care)

% condolence

% blessing (e.g. after a sneeze)

% politeness / appreciation (you-are-welcome family + "that's kind of you")

% gen295 (basic-chat cat.43 "Famiglia"): kinship terms as a lexical class, so
% mod_family recognizes a family statement ("my father …", "I have two brothers")
% and an honest self-decline ("what is your sister's name" — parrot0 is an AI, it
% has no family). Singular forms; the module singularizes plurals before the
% check. EN + IT so an Italian family statement engages through the same path.

% ═══ Parentela: fatti base + operatori (join + ricorsione) — gen335, learning mesh ═══
% Accanto a family_relation così il save-map instrada la parentela futura qui.

% ── PARENTAGE OPERATORS (ancestor, descendant, sibling, grandfather) (scattered from mesh-session.p0, gen335) ──
